<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>GSAT Governance Report</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-note">HSCS Governance Stress Test</div>
    <h1>Illustrative Governance Stress Test Report</h1>

    <p class="sub">
      Example output from a GSAT™ assessment conducted under transition conditions.
      Governance performance is evaluated across five domains and translated into structured supervisory outputs.
    </p>

    <div class="soft-block">
      <div class="section-title">Executive Summary</div>
      <p>
        A multi-entity transition environment introduced governance stress across escalation pathways,
        exposure visibility, and dependency concentration under simulated stress conditions.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-12">
        Governance was reclassified from structurally vulnerable to resilient following targeted
        realignment across escalation design, visibility integration, and dependency reduction.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="soft-block mt-16">
      <div class="section-title">Governance Scorecard</div>
      <div class="score-top mt-16">
        <div class="score-box">
          <div class="score-label">GSAT Score</div>
          <div class="score">17<span class="score-denom">/25</span></div>
          <div class="badge badge-orange">GRR-C → GRR-A</div>
        </div>

        <div class="score-box">
          <div class="score-label">Transmission Risk</div>
          <div class="score-small">High → Moderate</div>
          <div class="badge badge-amber">Reduced systemic exposure</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="soft-block mt-16">
      <div class="section-title">Key Findings</div>
      <p>Escalation pathways exhibited latency under stress conditions, limiting timely decision-making.</p>
      <p class="mt-10">Dependency concentration across key counterparties amplified transmission risk during stress scenarios.</p>
      <p class="mt-10">Fragmented visibility across entities reduced governance effectiveness under time compression.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="soft-block mt-16">
      <div class="section-title">Governance Realignment</div>
      <p>Escalation structures were redesigned to reduce latency and ensure direct access to decision authority.</p>
      <p class="mt-10">Exposure visibility was enhanced through integrated reporting across entities and clearing structures.</p>
      <p class="mt-10">Dependency concentration was reduced through diversification of counterparties and infrastructure providers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="soft-block mt-16">
      <div class="cta-title">Request Full Governance Stress Assessment</div>
      <p class="mt-12">
        This illustrative report reflects GSAT™ outputs under simulated conditions.
        Full assessments include supervisory calibration, data validation, and governance implementation support.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="index.html" class="btn btn-primary">Run Simulation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
